Test: Line Height and Leading

        /* Reset for consistency */
        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        body { font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; }

        /* Test container */
        .test-container {
            width: 700px;
            height: 800px;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }

        /* Test-specific CSS */
        .line-height-test {
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding: 15px;
            border: 1px dashed #999;
            background-color: white;
            width: 400px;
        }

        .test-title {
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            color: #333;
        }

        .text-sample {
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 5px;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }

        .line-height-normal {
            line-height: normal;
            background-color: #ffcccc;
        }

        .line-height-1 {
            line-height: 1;
            background-color: #ccffcc;
        }

        .line-height-1-5 {
            line-height: 1.5;
            background-color: #ccccff;
        }

        .line-height-2 {
            line-height: 2;
            background-color: #ffffcc;
        }

        .line-height-px {
            line-height: 40px;
            background-color: #ffccff;
        }

        .line-height-percent {
            line-height: 120%;
            background-color: #ccffff;
        }

        /* Inline mixing demonstration */
        .inline-mix {
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        .inline-large {
            font-size: 24px;
            background-color: #ffaaaa;
        }

        .inline-small {
            font-size: 12px;
            background-color: #aaffaa;
        }

        .inline-normal {
            font-size: 16px;
            background-color: #aaaaff;
        }

        /* Baseline grid visualization */
        .baseline-grid {
            background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent 0px, transparent 15px, #ff000020 15px, #ff000020 16px, transparent 16px, transparent 31px, #ff000020 31px, #ff000020 32px);
            background-size: 100% 32px;
            line-height: 2; /* 32px line height for 16px font */
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #999;
        }





            Line-height: normal

                This text uses the normal line-height, which is typically around 1.2 times the font size. This creates comfortable reading spacing.




            Line-height: 1 (no leading)

                This text uses line-height: 1, meaning no extra space between lines. Text may appear cramped with descenders touching ascenders.




            Line-height: 1.5

                This text uses line-height: 1.5, providing generous spacing between lines for improved readability.




            Line-height: 2 (double spacing)

                This text uses line-height: 2, creating double-spaced text like traditional typewritten documents.




            Line-height: 40px (fixed)

                This text uses a fixed line-height of 40px, regardless of font size changes.




            Mixed font sizes with line-height: 1.5

                Small text and 
                normal text and 
                large text all sharing the same line-height multiplier.




            Baseline grid visualization

                This text is laid out on a baseline grid. The red lines show where the baselines should align for consistent vertical rhythm.






